{"id": "EUVD-2025-9549", "enisaUuid": "15628cee-8c54-37b3-b2b0-4f0b1d50c213", "description": "A flaw was found in the Tempo Operator. When the Jaeger UI Monitor Tab functionality is enabled in a Tempo instance managed by the Tempo Operator, the Operator creates a ClusterRoleBinding for the Service Account of the Tempo instance to grant the cluster-monitoring-view ClusterRole.\nThis can be exploited if a user has 'create' permissions on TempoStack and 'get' permissions on Secret in a namespace (for example, a user has ClusterAdmin permissions for a specific namespace), as the user can read the token of the Tempo service account and therefore has access to see all cluster metrics.", "datePublished": "2025-04-02T11:09:55", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-20T20:42:20", "baseScore": 4.3, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-2842", "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2025-2842", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2355219", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2025:3607", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2025:3740"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-2842", "GHSA-5xf3-gmx4-529v"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "136c9f0d-4519-3c48-854b-4ddb553c1e21", "product": {"name": "Red Hat OpenShift distributed tracing 3.5.2"}, "product_version": "patch: sha256:be2ec2e3d3b21748cfe3b9382f7fc1f6c72d5f380fc97773518c254c6e5794ca"}, {"id": "1f2b433e-5c9d-3724-8501-70d8a2393649", "product": {"name": "Red Hat OpenShift distributed tracing 3.5.2"}, "product_version": "patch: sha256:29c1be152c9b2ca9fa8af25a10f156f8731b8396e8b2bc82d6b398a5e5027fdf"}, {"id": "38e52471-f055-3bd8-8abe-bb67aa560ea3", "product": {"name": "Red Hat OpenShift distributed tracing 3.5.2"}, "product_version": "patch: sha256:cbe0df797c34aebfec911c281fbfee9fe7713a4c45d778ae480cd6a7bcab202e"}, {"id": "62c5f572-c22d-3f76-8963-1b87c6617ff9", "product": {"name": "Red Hat OpenSh